# NEXUS TLS — Full Implementation Plan

Implementing the complete NEXUS TLS system as described in the implementation guide. This is a monorepo-based full-stack application with a Next.js frontend, FastAPI backend, shared packages, and DevOps infrastructure.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> This is a large-scale project (estimated 8 weeks for a 3-person team by the guide). I will scaffold the **entire codebase structure** and write all the source code files described in the guide. However, external service provisioning (Upstash Redis, Supabase, MaxMind, Vercel/Railway deployment, Grafana Cloud) requires your accounts and API keys — I'll create `.env.example` files with placeholders.

## User Review Required

> [!WARNING]
> **External Services**: The following require manual setup with your accounts. I will wire in placeholder config:
> - **Upstash Redis** — Create at [console.upstash.com](https://console.upstash.com)
> - **Supabase PostgreSQL** — Create at [supabase.com](https://supabase.com)
> - **MaxMind GeoIP2** — Register at [maxmind.com](https://www.maxmind.com)
> - **AbuseIPDB** — Get key from [abuseipdb.com](https://www.abuseipdb.com)
> - **Mapbox** — Get token from [mapbox.com](https://www.mapbox.com)
> - **Sentry** — Create project at [sentry.io](https://sentry.io)

> [!CAUTION]
> **Prerequisites on your machine**:
> - Node.js >= 20.x
> - Python >= 3.12
> - pnpm >= 9.x
> - Docker >= 24.x (for local dev with docker-compose)
>
> Please confirm you have these installed, or let me know which ones to skip.

---

