## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests

1. **Frontend build verification**:
   ```bash
   cd c:\Users\andri\Desktop\Nexus.v.0.1\apps\web
   pnpm install
   pnpm build
   ```
   Expected: Build completes without errors.

2. **Backend Python syntax check**:
   ```bash
   cd c:\Users\andri\Desktop\Nexus.v.0.1\apps\api
   python -m py_compile main.py
   python -m py_compile routers/session.py
   python -m py_compile services/risk_engine.py
   python -m py_compile services/geo_service.py
   python -m py_compile db/redis.py
   ```
   Expected: No syntax errors.

3. **Session Engine package build**:
   ```bash
   cd c:\Users\andri\Desktop\Nexus.v.0.1\packages\session-engine
   pnpm install
   pnpm build
   ```

### Manual Verification

1. **Structure verification**: After implementation, run `tree` on the project root to confirm all directories and files match the guide's architecture.
2. **Docker compose validation**: Run `docker-compose config` to verify the compose file is valid YAML.
3. **Dev server smoke test**: Run `pnpm dev` from root to verify the Next.js frontend starts successfully on `localhost:3000`.

> [!NOTE]
> Full end-to-end testing (login flows, session timeout, biometrics) requires external services (Redis, PostgreSQL) to be provisioned. I will focus on ensuring all code is syntactically correct, properly structured, and follows the guide exactly.
